          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F8CAFD10-50A3-4EFF-A518-805D9740736F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdevon-archer-testimony-house-oversight-james-comer-hunter-biden-joe-biden-8bc222ca&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">亨特·拜登的前商业伙伴德文·阿彻 (Devon Archer) 向众议院监督委员会闭门作证，讲述总统与其子的海外商业交易的关系，其中包括与商业伙伴通过免提电话进行了 20 多次通话。图片：路透社/美联社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div><p>所有人都知道，亨特·拜登与乌克兰和中国的能源公司合作开展利润丰厚的工作时，并没有出售他在能源市场的专业知识。但他卖的是什么？亨特的前商业伙伴德文·阿彻周一提供的答案是拜登的“品牌”。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>阿彻先生向众议院监督委员会闭门作证，我们正在等待笔录以查看他的完整证词。但根据监督委员会主席詹姆斯·科默发布的一份摘要，阿彻先生证实亨特正在宣传拜登家族的名字及其所暗示的政治机会。</p><p>考虑到我们已经了解到亨特·拜登与乌克兰能源公司 Burisma 和中国华信能源公司的合作，这并不奇怪。阿彻先生告诉委员会，亨特在商务会议期间让当时担任副总裁的父亲开免提电话超过 20 次，以推销“品牌”。</p><p>据科默先生的说法，阿彻先生认为，丑闻缠身的“如果没有‘品牌’，Burisma 就会倒闭”。科默表示，由于与拜登的关系，“人们会害怕合法地扰乱布里斯马公司”。</p><p>阿彻还证实，Burisma 高管向亨特施加了巨大压力，要求他利用他的关系来处理前乌克兰检察官维克托·肖金 (Viktor Shokin) 对公司的调查。乔·拜登公开宣称自己解雇了肖金，理由是调查腐败的检察官本人也腐败。</p><p>科默先生说，阿彻先生还告诉委员会，乔·拜登亲自参加了亨特在北京和华盛顿特区与中国和俄罗斯商人举行的其他商务会议。这与拜登总统声称他从未与儿子讨论过这些商业往来的说法相悖。</p><p>听取证词的民主党人丹·戈德曼 (Dan Goldman) 表示，阿彻先生告诉委员会，拜登夫妇从未在这些电话中讨论过业务，因此证词毫无意义。但亨特不太可能想和他的父亲谈论天气。他知道自己在卖什么，随着众议院的不断寻找，我们将看到我们还了解到什么。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 22:41:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-testimony-house-oversight-james-comer-hunter-biden-joe-biden-8bc222ca</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-testimony-house-oversight-james-comer-hunter-biden-joe-biden-8bc222ca<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>德文郡弓箭手</category><category>詹姆斯·科默</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>亨特·拜登</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nigel Farage Shows What Happens When Good Banks Go Woke]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>英国的一桩丑闻显示了金融武器化的实际情况。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590122021070373774"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590122021070373774"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 31 日下午 6:40 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/coutts-bank-u-k-nigel-farage-alison-rose-peter-flavel-a31c7f31"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-827106?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">奈杰尔·法拉奇</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：亚历克斯·布兰登/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这是你在美国几乎没有听说过的最大的金融丑闻：两名英国银行高管失去了工作，其他人可能也会因关闭客户账户的政治化决定而引起轩然大波。这对美国人来说是一个警示故事，告诉他们当优秀银行醒来时会发生什么。</p><p>顾资银行 (Coutts &amp; Co.) 的混乱始于 6 月底，当时奈杰尔·法拉奇 (Nigel Farage) 表示，这家独家私人银行将关闭他的账户。法拉奇先生是英国著名右翼政治家，是 2016 年英国脱欧公投的主要推动者，并在此前后表达了经济和社会保守观点。</p><p>法拉奇声称，他因政治原因而被取消银行业务，但该银行最初否认了这一说法。顾资银行母公司 NatWest 的首席执行官艾莉森·罗斯 (Alison Rose) 告诉 BBC 记者，法拉奇先生的最低余额要求低于顾资银行的高额要求。</p><p>事实证明法拉奇先生是对的。他获得了一份 40 页的银行内部讨论记录副本，内容涉及他的账户。顾资银行员工得出的结论是，继续为法拉奇先生提供银行服务将为顾资银行带来“重大声誉风险”，因为他有时在种族关系、俄罗斯和气候政策等问题上发表煽动性言论。档案记录员工承认，以其他方式保留法拉奇先生的账户是有商业理由的。</p><p>罗斯女士承认自己是 BBC 报道的消息来源后被迫辞职，该报道最初将泄密事件归咎于匿名消息来源。几天后，顾资银行首席执行官彼得·弗拉维尔（Peter Flavel）也跟进了此事，这是该银行试图从丑闻中恢复过来的一部分。总理里希·苏纳克正在考虑新的规定，以防止银行因客户的政治观点而将其拒之门外。</p><p>这个故事不仅仅是一场英国商业混乱，因为发生在顾资银行法拉奇先生身上的事情也可能发生在美国。随着新证据表明拜登政府与科技公司之间存在密切联系，以压制政治上不受欢迎的观点，美国也卷入了有关新冠病毒大流行的社交媒体审查丑闻。高管们知道政客和监管机构对其企业拥有巨大的权力，这增加了他们接受审查的动力。</p><p>出于类似的原因，大西洋两岸的金融机构都宣扬其自由主义文化信念，库茨关闭法拉奇先生账户的部分理由是，为他提供服务将“与我们作为包容性组织的立场相悖”。档案。</p><p>银行受到如此严格的监管，以至于它们在商业决策中不可避免地要考虑政治因素。 2008 年获得救助后，英国纳税人仍持有国民西敏寺银行 39% 的股份，人们普遍预计左翼工党将赢得明年的选举。在档案中，库茨银行的员工没有公开考虑过他们可能很快就会受到反对法拉奇先生的政客的监管，但很难想象有人没有想到过这种想法。</p><p>随着政治家更加依赖银行来实施他们的政策，这种危险将会加剧。如果银行面临华盛顿推动气候议程的压力，它会为净零气候政策的批评者保留账户吗？</p><p>普通企业可以选择客户，但银行已经很长时间没有成为普通企业了。左派尤其将银行视为公用事业。法拉奇事件暴露了这种情况的危险性，而且不仅仅是在英国。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=34FABCBA-64BF-4342-BE51-E7CF2E50F2C5&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fcoutts-bank-u-k-nigel-farage-alison-rose-peter-flavel-a31c7f31&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">仙境：美国19个州总检察长致函摩根大通，指责其歧视保守宗教团体。银行否认。美国的商业应该再次成为商业，而不是政治（05/17/23）。图片：Zuma Press/彭博新闻 综合：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 22:40:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/coutts-bank-uk-nigel-farage-alison-rose-peter-flavel-a31c7f31</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/coutts-bank-uk-nigel-farage-alison-rose-peter-flavel-a31c7f31<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>银行业</category><category>商业银行</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>私人银行/财富管理</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>库茨</category><category>奈杰尔·法拉奇</category><category>彼得·弗拉维尔</category><category>艾莉森·罗斯</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>银行业</category><category>商业银行</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>私人银行</category><category>财富管理</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Devon Archer Throws a Curve]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>乔·拜登对亨特及其笔记本电脑的否认现已被证实。他会在 2024 年总统辩论中说什么？ <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122243035880462"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122243035880462"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BI560_mcgurn_AM_20180807122138.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn" itemprop="url" rel="author">威廉·麦格恩</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 31 日下午 6:22 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-throws-a-curve-house-testimony-plea-deal-debate-biden-d5b85171"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826813?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乔·拜登 7 月 27 日在华盛顿发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>到目前为止，关于乔·拜登和 2024 年的最大问题是他是否能身体健康地参加辩论。但在亨特认罪失败后，亨特·拜登前商业伙伴德文·阿彻周一在众议院监督委员会作了闭门证词，引发了另一个问题：总统是否需要为在 2020 年辩论期间误导公众而道歉，当时他明确表示否认儿子海外权谋？</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>如果亨特的认罪协议没有在联邦法院破裂，这一切都会消失。检察官告诉法庭，亨特可能仍会被指控未注册为外国代理人。</p><p>然后是阿彻先生周一的证词。根据董事长詹姆斯·科默的一份声明，阿彻先生作证说，乔·拜登加入了与亨特客户、乌克兰能源巨头布里斯马公司的电话交谈，以“出售该品牌”。阿切尔先生进一步表示，布里斯马向亨特施压，要求他就检察官维克托·肖金(Viktor Shokin)的问题向“华盛顿特区”寻求帮助，而副总统拜登曾推动解雇他。</p><p>这并不能证明乔·拜登讨论了商业条款或分享了任何利润。但至少，它暴露了拜登在2020年对美国人民的操纵。</p><p>亨特在两次总统辩论中都占据了显着位置，因为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>不断提到他。第一次提及是在 9 月 29 日于克利夫兰举行的辩论中。在拜登先生批评特朗普总统的对华政策后，现任总统表示：</p><p> “中国吃了你的午餐，乔。难怪你儿子进去了，哇——他拿出了数十亿美元。他拿出数十亿美元来管理。他赚了数百万美元。而且，在我们讨论的过程中，为什么莫斯科市长的妻子只是出于好奇而给了你儿子 350 万美元？”</p><p>然后他问道：“他对布里斯马做了什么？”</p><p>拜登总共八次宣称“这不是真的”或类似的言论。他七次表示特朗普的主张“不可信”，有时“完全不可信”。接近尾声时，他补充道：“我儿子在布里斯马没有做错任何事。”</p><p>特朗普先生不会就此罢休：亨特“在乌克兰、中国、莫斯科和其他地方发了财”。拜登再次否认：“这根本不是真的。”</p><p>拜登指望媒体能够继续前进，而事实也基本上做到了。但随后拜登夫妇与玛丽莲·诺雷卡法官发生了冲突。她向亨特·拜登本人证实，与他父亲的说法相反，他确实从乌克兰和中国公司获得了一小笔财富。</p><p>然后是特朗普反复提及的 2014 年莫斯科前市长遗孀埃琳娜·巴图琳娜 (Elena Baturina) 的 350 万美元电汇。亨特的律师表示，他的客户对接收公司没有兴趣，也不是该公司的联合创始人。但阿彻先生与该公司有联系，而且他也知道亨特的交易是如何构建的。也许我们会从文字记录中了解更多信息。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>了解更多 大街</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">亨特·拜登的讨价还价请求</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 24 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/no-labels-equals-trump-manchin-lieberman-2024-election-biden-rematch-55feda8e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">“无标签”等于特朗普？</a> <span class="date">2023 年 7 月 17 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-ongoing-investigation-dodge-hunter-biden-david-weiss-bribe-question-informant-67c31868?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">针对亨特·拜登的“正在进行的调查”道奇</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 10 日</span></li></ul></div></div><p>拜登在 10 月 22 日的第二场辩论中继续表示绝对否认。特朗普再次不肯罢休。 “如果俄罗斯、乌克兰、中国、其他国家、伊拉克的情况属实，那么他就是一个腐败的政客，”他说。特朗普随后提到了“来自地狱的笔记本电脑”，促使拜登暗示这不是亨特的。</p><p> “你看，”他说，“有 50 名前国家情报人员说，他指控我的这件事是俄罗斯的计划。他们说这具有所有特征——四、五名中央情报局前负责人，双方都说他所说的是一堆垃圾。”</p><p>这也是不真实的。 The “50 former national intelligence folks” Mr. Biden invoked did suggest the laptop could be Russian disinformation. But we now know the laptop was Hunter&#39;s—and the former intel officials were the ones spreading disinformation.</p><p> In short Mr. Biden wasn&#39;t telling the truth about Hunter during the debates, and there is no way to defend those answers today. In the runup to next year&#39;s election, we are likely to learn even more as the congressional investigations continue.</p><p> Even the Biden White House recognizes that the president&#39;s blanket denials are no longer credible. No doubt it&#39;s why press secretary</p> Karine Jean-Pierre recently switched the official party line from “the president never discussed his son&#39;s business with him” to “the president has never been in business with him.”<p></p><p> The real danger for Mr. Biden in the 2024 debates is if the Republican candidate asks him the obvious: “Mr. President, we have learned since 2020 that almost everything you claimed about your son&#39;s business overseas the last time you were on this debate stage was untrue. Why should the American people believe anything you say now?”</p><p> <em>Write to mcgurn@wsj.com.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F8CAFD10-50A3-4EFF-A518-805D9740736F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdevon-archer-throws-a-curve-house-testimony-plea-deal-debate-biden-d5b85171&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Hunter Biden&#39;s former business partner, Devon Archer, has testified behind closed doors to the House Oversight Committee about the President&#39;s ties to his son&#39;s foreign business dealings, which included more than 20 calls on speaker phone with business associates. Images: Reuters/Associated Press Composite: Mark Kelly <span class="imageCredit">The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 22:22:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-throws-a-curve-house-testimony-plea-deal-debate-biden-d5b85171</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-throws-a-curve-house-testimony-plea-deal-debate-biden-d5b85171<author><![CDATA[William McGurn]]></author><category> hunter</category><category> china</category><category> ukraine</category><category> laptop</category><category> foreign deal</category><category> debate stage</category><category> testimony</category><category>总统</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Elections</category><category> National/Presidential Elections</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Hunter Biden</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>presidential elections</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Devon Archer Throws a Curve]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Joe Biden&#39;s denials about Hunter and his laptop are now disproven. What will he say in the 2024 presidential debates? <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122243035880462"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122243035880462"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BI560_mcgurn_AM_20180807122138.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-mcgurn" itemprop="url" rel="author">William McGurn</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 31, 2023 6:22 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/devon-archer-throws-a-curve-house-testimony-plea-deal-debate-biden-d5b85171"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-826813?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Joe Biden delivers remarks in Washington, July 27.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: JONATHAN ERNST/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Up to now the big question about Joe Biden and 2024 has been whether he&#39;ll be physically up for the debates. But former Hunter Biden business associate Devon Archer&#39;s closed-door testimony to the House Oversight Committee on Monday, on the heels of Hunter&#39;s failed plea, raises another question: Will the president have to apologize for misleading the public during the 2020 debates, when he categorically denied his son&#39;s influence-peddling overseas?</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> All this would have gone away if Hunter&#39;s plea agreement hadn&#39;t blown up in federal court. Prosecutors told the court that Hunter might still be charged with failing to register as a foreign agent.</p><p> Then came Mr. Archer&#39;s Monday testimony. According to a statement by Chairman James Comer, Mr. Archer testified that Joe Biden joined phone conversations with Ukrainian energy giant Burisma, a Hunter client, to “sell the brand.” Mr. Archer further said that Burisma pressured Hunter to get help from “DC” regarding prosecutor Viktor Shokin, for whose firing Vice President Biden pushed.</p><p> This doesn&#39;t prove Joe Biden discussed business terms or shared in any profits. But at the very least, it exposes Mr. Biden&#39;s gaslighting of the American people in 2020.</p><p> Hunter featured prominently in both presidential debates because <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> kept bringing him up. The first mention came in the Sept. 29 debate in Cleveland. After Mr. Biden criticized President Trump&#39;s China policy, the incumbent said:</p><p> “China ate your lunch, Joe. And no wonder your son goes in and, wha—he takes out billions of dollars. He takes out billions of dollars to manage. He makes millions of dollars. And also, while we&#39;re at it, why is it just out of curiosity, the mayor of Moscow&#39;s wife gave your son 3½ million dollars?”</p><p> He then asked: “What did he do with Burisma?”</p><p> Altogether Mr. Biden declared “that is not true” or words to that effect eight times. He said seven times that Mr. Trump&#39;s assertions were “discredited,” sometimes “totally discredited.” Near the end he added, “My son did nothing wrong at Burisma.”</p><p> Mr. Trump wouldn&#39;t let it rest: Hunter “made a fortune in Ukraine, in China, in Moscow and various other places.” Mr. Biden again denied it: “That is simply not true.”</p><p> Mr. Biden counted on a compliant press to move on, and it largely did. But then the Bidens came up against Judge Maryellen Noreika. She confirmed with Hunter Biden himself that, contrary to his father&#39;s assertions, he did receive a small fortune from Ukrainian and Chinese firms.</p><p> Then there&#39;s the $3.5 million 2014 wire transfer from Elena Baturina, widow of the former Moscow mayor, that Mr. Trump harped on. Hunter&#39;s lawyer has said his client had no interest in and wasn&#39;t a co-founder of the recipient firm. But Mr. Archer is linked to the firm—and he also knows how Hunter&#39;s deals were structured. Maybe we&#39;ll learn more from the transcript. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More Main Street</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-joe-bargain-plea-tax-irs-whistleblower-archer-ziegler-shapley-burisma-5f891342?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Hunter Biden&#39;s Bargain Plea</a> <span class="date">July 24, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/no-labels-equals-trump-manchin-lieberman-2024-election-biden-rematch-55feda8e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;No Labels&#39; Equals Trump?</a> <span class="date">July 17, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-ongoing-investigation-dodge-hunter-biden-david-weiss-bribe-question-informant-67c31868?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">The &#39;Ongoing Investigation&#39; Dodge on Hunter Biden</a> <span class="date">July 10, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> Mr. Biden continued issuing absolute denials in the second debate, on Oct. 22. Again Mr. Trump wouldn&#39;t let it rest. “If this stuff is true about Russia, Ukraine, China, other countries, Iraq—if this is true, then he&#39;s a corrupt politician,” he said. Mr. Trump then brought up the “laptop from hell,” prompting Mr. Biden to imply it wasn&#39;t Hunter&#39;s.</p><p> “Look,” he said, “there are 50 former national intelligence folks who said that what this, he&#39;s accusing me of, is a Russian plan. They have said that this has all the characteristics—four—five former heads of the CIA, both parties, say what he&#39;s saying is a bunch of garbage.”</p><p> This was also untrue. The “50 former national intelligence folks” Mr. Biden invoked did suggest the laptop could be Russian disinformation. But we now know the laptop was Hunter&#39;s—and the former intel officials were the ones spreading disinformation.</p><p> In short Mr. Biden wasn&#39;t telling the truth about Hunter during the debates, and there is no way to defend those answers today. In the runup to next year&#39;s election, we are likely to learn even more as the congressional investigations continue.</p><p> Even the Biden White House recognizes that the president&#39;s blanket denials are no longer credible. No doubt it&#39;s why press secretary</p> Karine Jean-Pierre recently switched the official party line from “the president never discussed his son&#39;s business with him” to “the president has never been in business with him.”<p></p><p> The real danger for Mr. Biden in the 2024 debates is if the Republican candidate asks him the obvious: “Mr. President, we have learned since 2020 that almost everything you claimed about your son&#39;s business overseas the last time you were on this debate stage was untrue. Why should the American people believe anything you say now?”</p><p> <em>Write to mcgurn@wsj.com.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
